post_text: Beginning Tuesday, May 5, GCPS will shift meal services to 1 day a week. On Tuesdays for the rest of the school year, we will distribute meal packs with 7 breakfasts and 7 lunches. This shift will reduce risk to our staff & increase the number of meals provided to students.

post_text:
GCPS and Granville County leaders have been working to find ways to feed our children over Spring Break (April 10-17). How can YOU help? In order to feed all of our students, we need to raise funds and we need volunteers to help distribute meals. Volunteers are needed to prep meals at FBC Creedmoor & West Oxford Baptist Church, help transport meals to distribution sites and distribute meals. Want to make a monetary donation? Head to Union Bank and indicate to the teller that the donation is for the School Feeding program. Donations are tax deductible.

Sign up here: https://bit.ly/GranvilleVolunteers

The National Weather Service has issued a Winter Weather Advisory for our area beginning tomorrow.
